This paper deals with routing end-to-end traffic over multiple paths in wireless mesh networks, which is a problem in the field of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also introduces a heuristic for path determination, which involves optimization and algorithm design (cs.IT). The paper conducts extensive computational experiments, which involves data analysis and statistical modeling (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the impact of the heuristic on network-wide throughput, which involves performance evaluation and optimization (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of interference in wireless mesh networks, which is a topic in the field of signal processing and communication (cs.SI).
